# AKOS Area Governance

Use this rule when chartering or maturing an O5-1 area under
`docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/`, or when running an I93
harmonization sweep. Codifies operator decision **D-IH-93-B** (area-
governance meta-process as the 17th Quality Fabric specialty, 2026-06-04).
Mechanical companion to
[`AREA_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/AREA_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md).

This rule does **not** replace the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar agents inherit when touching area
folders, area processes, or area charter markdown.

## When this rule applies

A sweep is in scope when **any** of:

- A new O5-1 area folder or area charter is minted (DATA at I93 P1 is the
  first worked example — do not author Data charter in P0-only work).
- A tranche adds `process_list.csv` / `baseline_organisation.csv` rows for
  an area.
- The operator requests `--matrix` before a harmonization commit (P8).

Out of scope: chore-only link fixes with no area-structure change.

## RULE 1 — Run the 14-component matrix before area CSV commits (binding)

Before landing an area CSV tranche or charter commit, run:

```powershell
py scripts/validate_area_completeness.py --matrix
```

Disposition every `gap` or `blocked` finding via inline-ratify per the
canonical §4. Do not treat a green People row as proof all areas are ready.

## RULE 2 — Conservative evidence posture (binding)

- **AREA-10** (Supabase mirrors): emit `skip` at P0 unless mirror evidence
  is explicitly in scope — do not invent PASS from repo-only scans.
- **Marketing**: `process_list.csv` uses area code `MKT`, not `Marketing`.

## RULE 3 — Pattern inheritance on new area processes (binding)

New area-governance processes MUST set
`inherited_pattern_id=pattern_area_buildout` on the `process_list.csv` row
unless a narrower pattern is operator-ratified in `DECISION_REGISTER.csv`.

